stylometry:
Standard deviation is important because it shows how close, or how far away the answers are from the mean.  The further the standard deviation is from the mean, or the higher the standard deviation is, the more likely there will be error, and it becomes more risky.  The closer the standard deviation is from the mean, and the lower the number is, eliminates the immense amount of riskiness and the chances for error. 

Standard deviation, when looking at simulation models, provides an excellent tool for decision making.  It can help a company realize how risky they are willing to be.
